<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="59">
Anostomidae currently includes 12 genera and approximately 140 species. It includes small fishes of less than 100 mm standard length and larger species up to 400 mm SL, the latter usually included in commercial and subsistence fisheries (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Géry">Gery</normalizedToken>
, 1977; Garavello &amp; Britski, 2003). The genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1BC503E5-0CEA-43D3-BE69-7C5802B677A2" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Anostomoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Anostomoides Pellegrin 1909:346" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Anostomoides</taxonomicName>
has only two valid species: 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D8052E2A-E05F-49D9-9FD0-D1827E320E79" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Anostomoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Anostomoides atrianalis Pellegrin 1908:346 [5]" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atrianalis">A. atrianalis</taxonomicName>
, of small adult size (~200 mm SL), and so far recorded only from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="río">rio</normalizedToken>
Orinoco, and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Anostomoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laticeps">A. laticeps</taxonomicName>
, a larger species that attains ca. 400 mm SL of wide distribution in the Amazon Basin. During ecological studies conducted by one of the authors (JZ) in the lower rio Xingu rapids, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pará">Para</normalizedToken>
State, several specimens of an undescribed species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1BC503E5-0CEA-43D3-BE69-7C5802B677A2" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Anostomoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Anostomoides Pellegrin 1909:346" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="59" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Anostomoides</taxonomicName>
were collected. The fish were readily distinguished by their conspicuous color pattern and are herein described as a new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
